<br>
what hes saying makes sense and you all know it...  If you're in a grp the only time your pet should get healed is after every other player is healed (yah even rangers :P ) You honestly feel that in a choice over who to heal a OOM wizard or a lvl 62 water pet the pet should take precedence?? Come on. <br>
<br>
Now I know Zarros and he's not &quot;anti-mage&quot; or anything lol just saying what we all know should and does happen. If mage, shaman and cleric are grouped you bet your ass the clerics healing the pets but if your in a standard grp and pet is just tanking an add cleric might not have time to heal and you should be ready for that. <br>
<br>
What you should be doing when you get an add with a grp is move it away from grp and mem 57 earth and get ready to chain that on it so you can at least control the add. your grp will be there to help you in no more than 2 mins and you can keep that up pretty easy... the slower will usually get a chance to slow your mob so its np.<br>
<br>
Now from a whole group of people that have made many levels sacrificing pets to mobs by the thousands (chain petting) for you to demand heals when the situation it tight (usually the only time your pet in a group would need a heal) is ridiculous. <br>
<br>
Just ask yourself whats better. A cleric that is OOM before the fights over and heals are still needed or a mage thats oom after the fight and can can recharge it in what like 2 mins tops?<br>
